   Technology Challenges


     No. of mod. Angular HPD Eff. Area @ 1 keV (cm^2 ) per mod. Mass (kg)
                               per mod. Notes
     Chandra 1 0.5" 1,000 1,000 Ground and polished Zerodur glass shells
               XMM-Newton 3 15" 1,500 420 Replicated Ni shells
              Astro-E 5 90" 400 12 Replicated aluminum segments
        Constellation-X 4 15" 7,500 420 Material and technology under
                              study/development
   Generation-X 6 0.1" 250,000 3,000 Materials and fabrication technology
                              to be determined
    Required Generation-X parameters in comparison with the state of the
    arts of X-ray mirror technologies circa 2000. Except for Chandra, the
   relevant parameters listed in the table are for each module. HPD stands
                          for half-power diameter.
